File: Durban businesswoman Sandra Moonsamy had been missing since May. DURBAN - The four suspects arrested in connection with the kidnapping of Sandra Moonsamy are appearing in the Durban magistrate's court on Monday.
The businesswoman was snatched out of her car in May in Pinetown, Kwa-Zulu Natal. After an intensive Hawks investigation, she was found bound at a house in eMalahleni on Thursday. READ: Missing Durban businesswoman found in chains Moonsamy's abductors allegedly demanded millions in ransom. Three luxury vehicles worth R3-million and a firearm have been seized for further investigation. Authorities are liaising with Interpol to find out if the suspects -- aged between 30 and 34 -- are wanted outside the country.